## Testing Approach

### Phase 1 (Visual Polish)
- Manual visual inspection: zoom in/out and verify grid fades smoothly
- Draw doodles and compare curve smoothness before/after
- Verify blur looks correct on both light and dark themes
- Test on mobile Safari (backdrop-filter has known quirks)

### Phase 2 (Interactions)
- Place 5+ snippets rapidly -- verify each gets a different rotation/offset
- Select an object, press "Remove" -- verify poof animation plays, then object disappears
- On a touch device: two-finger tap should undo last doodle; three-finger tap should redo
- Verify pinch-to-zoom still works after gesture shortcut changes (regression test)

### Phase 3 (Ambient Shadow)
- Move mouse over canvas -- verify light gradient follows smoothly
- Move mouse off canvas -- verify light fades out
- Switch between dark and light themes -- verify appropriate light color
- Check mobile: touch and drag on canvas, verify no jank

### Phase 4 (Pie Menu)
- Long-press an object on mobile -- pie menu appears
- Right-click an object on desktop -- pie menu appears
- Click a pie menu item -- action executes, menu closes
- Click outside pie menu -- menu closes
- Verify pie menu position stays within canvas bounds (clamp if near edge)

### Phase 5 (Real-time)
- Edit a canvas, move objects -- verify debounced PATCH calls in Network tab
- Open same canvas in two tabs -- verify changes propagate
- Verify existing save flow still works for new canvases
- Load an old canvas document -- verify no regressions

